        <title>Whims for a Wedding</title>
        <published>2024-12-29T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2024-12-29T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://berdandy.com/blog/goldsmithing/"/>
        <id>https://berdandy.com/blog/goldsmithing/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://berdandy.com/blog/goldsmithing/">&lt;p&gt;When I decided to ask Rachel if she wanted to get married, I wanted something unique and personal for an
engagement ring. With the audacity of curiosity, I wandered into a &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;bellchamber.net&#x2F;&quot;&gt;local goldsmith&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&#x27;s
shop with the intention of asking for some advice on how to explore making the engagement ring
myself.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serendipity was with me that day, because it turned out that Jason had previously taught workshops,
but hadn&#x27;t in several years. He was open to doing some custom lessons about lost-wax casting.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fast-forward several months, a few dozen lunchtime lessons later, and I had created an
engagement ring in my own custom claddagh design&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;&#x2F;pages&#x2F;craft&#x2F;metalwork_engagement_ring.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;berdandy.com&#x2F;pages&#x2F;craft&#x2F;metalwork_engagement_ring.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;metalwork_engagement_ring&quot; width=&quot;240&quot; height=&quot;240&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; &#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;... and two wedding bands with line work that evokes a similar feeling:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;&#x2F;pages&#x2F;craft&#x2F;metalwork_wedding_bands.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;berdandy.com&#x2F;pages&#x2F;craft&#x2F;metalwork_wedding_bands.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;metalwork_wedding_bands&quot; width=&quot;240&quot; height=&quot;240&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; &#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
</content>
        
    </entry>
